{"info": {"author": "Sylvain Fankhauser", "author_email": "sephi@fhtagn.top", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8"], "description": "=============================\nMatrix SAML hostname stripper\n=============================\n\nThis mapping provider strips the ``@domain.com`` part from UIDs coming from a SAML2\nidentity provider (IDP). This is useful for example when `using Google Apps as\nan IDP <https://support.google.com/a/answer/6087519?hl=en>`_, to avoid getting\nMatrix IDs like ``jane.doe=40domain.com@domain.com`` (instead you'll get\n``jane.doe@domain.com``).\n\n**Note:** At the time of this writing, the `support for user-configurable\nmapping providers <https://github.com/matrix-org/synapse/pull/6411>`_ hasn't\nbeen released yet. You will probably have to wait for Synapse 1.7 or 1.8, or\ninstall an unreleased version of Synapse.\n\n------------\nInstallation\n------------\n\nRun the following command in the same virtual environment of your Synapse install:\n\n``pip install matrix-saml-strip-hostname``\n\nThen edit the ``homeserver.yaml`` file on your Synapse install to use the new\nmapping provider::\n\n  saml2_config:\n    user_mapping_provider:\n      module: matrix_saml_strip_hostname.mapping_providers.StripHostnameSamlMappingProvider\n\n-------------\nConfiguration\n-------------\n\nThis mapper inherits from `the default mapping provider\n<https://github.com/matrix-org/synapse/blob/fc316a4894912f49f5d0321e533aabca5624b0ba/docs/saml_mapping_providers.md#synapses-default-provider>`_.\nIt will first strip the hostname, and then pass the result to the\n``synapse.handlers.saml_handler.DefaultSamlMappingProvider`` mapping provider.\nThere is no support for disabling this post-processing.\n\nRefer to `the default configuration file\n<https://github.com/matrix-org/synapse/blob/fc316a4894912f49f5d0321e533aabca5624b0ba/docs/sample_config.yaml#L1272>`_\nfor configuration options for the default provider.\n", "description_content_type": "text/x-rst", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/sephii/matrix-saml-strip-hostname", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "matrix-saml-strip-hostname", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/matrix-saml-strip-hostname/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/matrix-saml-strip-hostname/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/sephii/matrix-saml-strip-hostname", "Repository": "https://github.com/sephii/matrix-saml-strip-hostname"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/matrix-saml-strip-hostname/0.1.3/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": ">=3.5", "summary": "SAML mapping provider to strip hostnames from mxids", "version": "0.1.3", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <p>This mapping provider strips the <tt>@domain.com</tt> part from UIDs coming from a SAML2\nidentity provider (IDP). This is useful for example when <a href=\"https://support.google.com/a/answer/6087519?hl=en\" rel=\"nofollow\">using Google Apps as\nan IDP</a>, to avoid getting\nMatrix IDs like <tt>jane.doe=40domain.com@domain.com</tt> (instead you\u2019ll get\n<tt>jane.doe@domain.com</tt>).</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> At the time of this writing, the <a href=\"https://github.com/matrix-org/synapse/pull/6411\" rel=\"nofollow\">support for user-configurable\nmapping providers</a> hasn\u2019t\nbeen released yet. You will probably have to wait for Synapse 1.7 or 1.8, or\ninstall an unreleased version of Synapse.</p>\n<div id=\"installation\">\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Run the following command in the same virtual environment of your Synapse install:</p>\n<p><tt>pip install <span class=\"pre\">matrix-saml-strip-hostname</span></tt></p>\n<p>Then edit the <tt>homeserver.yaml</tt> file on your Synapse install to use the new\nmapping provider:</p>\n<pre>saml2_config:\n  user_mapping_provider:\n    module: matrix_saml_strip_hostname.mapping_providers.StripHostnameSamlMappingProvider\n</pre>\n</div>\n<div id=\"configuration\">\n<h2>Configuration</h2>\n<p>This mapper inherits from <a href=\"https://github.com/matrix-org/synapse/blob/fc316a4894912f49f5d0321e533aabca5624b0ba/docs/saml_mapping_providers.md#synapses-default-provider\" rel=\"nofollow\">the default mapping provider</a>.\nIt will first strip the hostname, and then pass the result to the\n<tt>synapse.handlers.saml_handler.DefaultSamlMappingProvider</tt> mapping provider.\nThere is no support for disabling this post-processing.</p>\n<p>Refer to <a href=\"https://github.com/matrix-org/synapse/blob/fc316a4894912f49f5d0321e533aabca5624b0ba/docs/sample_config.yaml#L1272\" rel=\"nofollow\">the default configuration file</a>\nfor configuration options for the default provider.</p>\n</div>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6939090, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "06b10c6723c7d9046eb0467ce2c247f3", "sha256": "a8b4ff9f792d3f07a93df0eb5beafdf111a0669b04005cc589578c6489fa413d"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "matrix_saml_strip_hostname-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "06b10c6723c7d9046eb0467ce2c247f3", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.5", "size": 1712, "upload_time": "2019-12-11T14:21:03", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-12-11T14:21:03.484544Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/54/23/86075e1d9b141823827550d9d05b664e6dc8fffdb0e6246b1707974514d1/matrix_saml_strip_hostname-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "492f3046899717f6f86338ca121c956c", "sha256": "ee125d0c6aaa7b6d355622c5c99d73a8c2ae1d5accd6a8baab5b8a78e3e9b8